      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>
               Indicating that the book belongs to 1) an institution; 2) an individual. Various shapes of these notes are possible, from rubricated and very regular, 
               written in the main hands, to less formal notes in the margins, written in crude hands (also without the formula <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘ</foreign>). 
            </p>
            <p>Examples are:
               <list>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESaqg010"/>, f. 99v: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገድለ፡ ሐዋርያት፡ ዘአድ፡ ቍልቋል፡</foreign>;</p>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmy002"/>, f. 2r: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝንቱ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘደብረ፡ ማእጾ፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ውጉዝ፡ ለይኩን፡ </foreign>;</p>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESdd015a"/>, f. 211v: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአባ፡ ሀብተ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ዘሠረቆ...</foreign>;</p>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESmma008"/>, f. 121b: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሐፍ፡ ዘአቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ ስምዖን።</foreign>;</p>
                  </item>
                  <item>
                     <p>
                        <ref type="mss" corresp="ESbmqm010"/>, f. 48ra: <foreign xml:lang="gez">አቡነ፡ ወልደ፡ አነንያ፡ ወምስለ፡ አመቱ፡ ወለተ፡ ሥላሴ፡</foreign>.</p>
                  </item>
               </list>
            </p>
